\f0\fs24 \cf0 # CODEX CREDENTIALS + EXTERNAL SETUP HANDOFF CHECKLIST\
\
Use this checklist when you reach integration points that need my help.\
\
## 1. Google Document AI\
Needed for:\
- primary OCR / HTR on scanned logbooks\
- handwriting / form extraction\
\
Ask me for:\
- Google Cloud Project ID\
- Document AI location\
- Processor ID\
- service account credential strategy\
\
Tell me to do:\
1. open Google Cloud Console\
2. create/select project\
3. enable Document AI API\
4. create a processor suitable for OCR / form parsing\
5. create a service account\
6. grant required roles\
7. create secure credentials\
8. give you:\
   - GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT_ID\
   - DOCUMENT_AI_LOCATION\
   - DOCUMENT_AI_PROCESSOR_ID\
   - GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS secret path or mounted secret content\
\
## 2. AWS\
Needed for:\
- storage\
- background jobs\
- optional Textract fallback\
- queues\
- notifications if used\
\
Ask me for:\
- AWS access key / secret or IAM role strategy\
- region\
- bucket names\
- queue names\
- Textract enablement if used\
\
Potential env vars:\
- AWS_REGION\
- AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID\
- AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY\
- S3_BUCKET_DOCUMENTS\
- S3_BUCKET_PROCESSED\
- SQS_QUEUE_DOCUMENTS\
- SQS_QUEUE_PRIORITY\
- SQS_QUEUE_DLQ\
\
## 3. OpenAI\
Needed for:\
- structured extraction reasoning\
- embeddings\
- answer synthesis\
\
Ask me for:\
- OPENAI_API_KEY\
\
Potential env vars:\
- OPENAI_API_KEY\
- OPENAI_MODEL_EXTRACT\
- OPENAI_MODEL_VISION\
- OPENAI_MODEL_EMBEDDINGS\
\
## 4. Supabase or current DB/runtime secrets\
Needed only if the current codebase uses it in production and you must extend existing models / storage.\
\
Ask me for:\
- Supabase URL\
- service role key\
- anon key if needed\
- DB connection string if direct DB access is needed\
- storage bucket names if relevant\
\
Potential env vars:\
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL\
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY\
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY\
- DATABASE_URL\
\
## 5. Auth provider\
Needed only if auth/org claims need extension.\
\
Ask me for:\
- auth provider domain\
- client id\
- client secret\
- signing / audience settings if applicable\
\
## 6. FAA provider configuration\
Important:\
Do not assume I can hand you one perfect FAA AD API key.\
\
Your job:\
- first support public-source ingestion through an abstraction\
- only ask me for credentials if a chosen FAA source or partner source requires them\
\
If source access is needed, tell me exactly:\
- what source\
- why\
- whether it is official or fallback\
- what account or approval is needed\
\
## 7. Email / notifications\
Only if reminder emails or compliance notifications are being wired now.\
\
Ask me for:\
- provider choice\
- API key\
- sender domain\
- sender address\
\
## 8. Stripe\
Only if billing work is touched in this phase.\
\
Ask me for:\
- publishable key\
- secret key\
- webhook secret\
- product / price IDs if already created\
\
## Rule for every credential request\
Do not just say \'93I need credentials.\'94\
Say:\
- exactly which service\
- exactly why\
- exact console steps\
- exact variable names\
- exact verification step}